                56
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Page 2 of 3 "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                67,
                936,
                176,
                954
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "title",
            "content": {
                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Interference Calculations on a shared Network file "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                94,
                85,
                594,
                104
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The inherent table locking schemes used in the Borland database engine does not allow users to carry out simultaneous interference calculations. An interference calculation creates a set of tables which relate to the network gr4 file. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                94,
                109,
                435,
                214
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "The June 02, 2002 program build allows the user to specify a private directory for interference calculations. The selection is made at the start of an interference calculation. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                94,
                228,
                436,
                298
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Operations such as specifying fade correlation will fail if the current network file does not match the database tables in the private directory. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                94,
                312,
                438,
                383
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "content": {
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/6241fddf026b6454ee1de892dea4a55988d9856b50d36abae4ec44092845c42a.jpg"
                },
                "content": "Interference\nCoordination Distance (km) 200.0\nMaximum frequency Separation (MHz) 150.0\nDefault Minimum Interference Level (dBm) -115.0\nMargin (dB) 10.0\nDigital Interference Objective\nThreshold degradation - multipath (dB) 1.0\nAnalyze current file only\nSub network intra system interference\nSub network against network interference\nIgnore diversity antennas\nIgnore adjacent channels\nInterference Calculation Directory\nUse network file directory\nUse private directory\nC:\\TEMP Browse",
